h3. Problem Definition
There is a Misleading Recommended Filter Query in the document *[Using Manage Sprints permission for advanced cases | https://confluence.atlassian.com/adminjiraserver/using-manage-sprints-permission-for-advanced-cases-938847165.html]* across all versions of the Doc both Cloud and Server

The following section is highly situational and misleading as an overall suggestion:
{quote}
In summary, we recommend that queries contain OR clauses in which AND clauses can be sub-clauses, and not the other way around.

Simply put, make sure:

your OR clauses are outside the brackets, and
your AND clauses sub-clauses are inside the brackets.
Recommended query format: <clause> OR (<clause> AND <clause>) OR <clause> OR (<clause> AND <clause>)

Complex query format: <clause> AND (<clause> OR <clause>) AND (<clause> OR <clause>)
{quote} 

as an EXE for the "Recommended query format: <clause> OR (<clause> AND <clause>) OR <clause> OR (<clause> AND <clause>)" query if any of these sections were missing a project definition it would be complex and should be rewritten as:
{code}
<project clause> OR (<project clause> AND <clause>) OR <project clause> OR (<project clause> AND <clause>)
{code}

This is only useful for passing in multiple projects where some of the projects have an additional restriction such as a component:
{code}
Project = projectA OR (Project = projectB AND component = test) OR Project = projectC OR (Project = projectD and Component = test)
{code}

The Logic of OR clauses connecting groupings of bracked queries is still good but the project association in each section is the main factor  Another example of this logic witha  simpler filter to collect the same data as the one above would be as follows noting (clause) OR (Clause) but a defined Project set at each section:
{code}
(Project in (projectA,projectC)) or (Project in (projectB,projectD) AND component = test)
{code}

NEXT the statement *"your AND clauses sub-clauses are inside the brackets."* with the example Query *"Complex query format: <clause> AND (<clause> OR <clause>) AND (<clause> OR <clause>)"* is only partially correct as an example the following Logic is *NOT COMPLEX* and project A and B would be applied to all the following OR subclauses:
{code}
(Project in (projectA,projectB) AND (<clause1> OR <clause2> OR <clause3> OR <clause4>)
{code}
As a comparison to how the AND outside the Brackets is a more valid solution Using the Current recommendation of the documentation the query above with the *"(project clause) AND (multiple or clauses without project associations)"* would be written as the following if using the "(clause) OR (Clause And Clause)" format:
{code}
(Project = projectA and Clause1) OR (Project = projectA and Clause2) OR (Project = projectA and Clause3) OR (Project = projectB and Clause1) OR (Project = projectB and Clause2) OR (Project = projectB and Clause3) OR (Project = projectB and Clause4)
{code}

h3. Suggested Solution
The major stress point of the examples needs to be stated in a way that more clearly indicates the Project association needs to be distributed across every OR section or uniquely defined in each OR section

Also the AND clause outside the Brackets with OR clause inside the brackets is also a good approach to simplify the JQL as long as the Project definition is passed to the OR clause via the AND clause as a *"(project clause) AND (multiple or clauses without project associations)"*
